---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="About" path="/about">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="tagline">What Macddaddy is, and what it isn't.</p>
  </section>

  <p>
    Macddaddy is a small, owner-operated systematic trading book. Strategies
    are designed, backtested, and walk-forward validated before any capital
    is committed. Picks are debated by an automated review pipeline before
    they fire; overrides happen, but they are logged.
  </p>

  <h2>The research process</h2>
  <p>
    Every signal goes through three checks before it earns capital:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>A clean in-sample backtest beating SPY by a meaningful margin.</li>
    <li>A walk-forward split with Sharpe positively correlated across halves.</li>
    <li>An honest accounting of fees, slippage, and turnover drag.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Raw return is a vanity metric. Risk-adjusted return (Sharpe, max drawdown)
    is what drives whether a signal is shipped.
  </p>

  <h2>What this site is</h2>
  <p>
    A public window onto the sleeve performance and the research that backs
    it. No live positions, no fills, no signals. Just outcomes and writeups.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
  <p style="color: var(--fg-dim); font-size: 0.875rem;">
    Nothing on this site is investment advice. Past performance does not
    guarantee future results. Systematic strategies can and do lose money.
  </p>
</Base>
